";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"srdjan\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5004:\"<p>We have just released <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/buddypress-multilingual/\">Buddypress Multilingual 1.5.5</a>.<br />\nIf you are not familiar with what BuddyPress Multilingual does &#8211; it allows BuddyPress sites to run fully multilingual using the WPML plugin.</p>\n<p>This release brings the following changes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Adds language switching to all BuddyPress pages (Activity, Groups, Profile and Register page)</li>\n<li>Allows to select the language when viewing user profiles</li>\n<li>Keeps the language consistent when clicking on different links (by adding the language to links)</li>\n<li>Allows to translate email notifications</li>\n<li>Keeps the entire BuddyPress workflow in the current language (create group, change avatars etc.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In the following images, you can see some of the new improvements¬†(note the captions)</p>\n<p>If you have any issues with BuddyPress Multilingual, or you&#8217;d like us to add missing features, please drop us¬†a line here.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_1159089\" style=\"width: 160px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/screenshot-1.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-1159089 size-thumbnail\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/screenshot-1-150x103.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"103\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/screenshot-1-150x103.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/screenshot-1-300x206.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2