erarchy\" class=\"toc-heading\" tabindex=\"-1\">Page Templates within the Template Hierarchy #<span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Page Templates within the Template Hierarchy</span></h3>\r\nWhen a person browses to your website, WordPress selects which template to use for rendering that page. As we learned earlier in the¬†Template Hierarchy, WordPress looks for template files in the following order:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong>Page¬†Template ‚Äî</strong>¬†If the page has a custom template assigned, WordPress looks for that file and, if found, uses it.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong><code>page-{slug}.php</code>¬†‚Äî</strong>¬†If no custom template has been assigned,¬†WordPress looks for and uses¬†a specialized template that contains the¬†page‚Äôs slug.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong><code>page-{id}.php</code>¬†‚Äî</strong>¬†If a specialized¬†template that includes the page‚Äôs slug is not found,¬†WordPress looks for and uses a specialized template named with the page‚Äôs ID.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong><code>page.php</code>¬†‚Äî</strong>¬†If a specialized template that includes the page‚Äôs ID is not found,¬†WordPress looks for and uses the theme‚Äôs default page template.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong><code>index.php</code>¬†‚Äî</strong>¬†If no specific page templates are assigned or found, WordPress defaults back to using the theme‚Äôs index file to render pages.</li>\r\n</ol>','Astringent','','publish','closed','closed','','astringent','','','2016-08-01 11:42:52','2016-08-01 11:42:52','',0,'http://dickinsons.dev/?page_id=50',0,'page','',0),(51,1,'2016-08-01 03:25:35','2016-08-01 03:25:35','<strong><a class=\"row-title\" href=\"http://dickinsons-vn.martintutko.com/wp-admin/post.php?post=20&amp;action=edit\">Astringent</a></strong>','Astringent','','inherit','closed','closed','','50-revision-v1','','','2016-08-01 03:25:35','2016-08-01 03:25:35','',50,'http://dickinsons.dev/uncategorized/50-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(52,1,'2016-08-01 03:25:48','2016-08-01 03:25:48','<strong><a class=\"row-title\